ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÙ
   Includes both 16 bit DOS and 32 bit WIN95/NT versions (GAC_BJ32.EXE)!
   
   Tournament FreeCell is an impressive addition to any BBS.  This game is
   especially well suited to multinode BBS systems, since it allows players
   on multiple nodes to participate in the game at the same time.  

   FreeCell is an addictive solitare card game, the object is to move all
   of your cards from the columns to the 4 Home Cells.  The trick is that
   the cards in the Home Cells must be in order by suit.  See the
   instructions inside of FreeCell for more information.

   Since the games can be long, a save option is available for the user.
   This will allow the user to continue a game at a later date in case they
   run out of time on your system or just need to stop.  This option also
   protects the user's game if they are disconnected from the system.

   This BBS game also supports Inter-BBS playing through the fidonet
   technology.  This game uses a routing system identical to Inter-LORD and
   very similiar to BREs HOST routing system.  All routing is handled by
   the League Coordinator.

   For quick installation, see the INSTALLATION section.  

   BBS SUPPORT:

	The following BBS Systems are automatically supported.  If your
	system is not listed, please notify me, and send me the format of
	your dropfile (or find a converter)

	- Remote Access                 - Renegade
	- QuickBBS                      - PC-Board
	- Maximus                       - Opus
	- Wildcat!                      - WWIV
	- Spitfire                      - SuperBBS
	- Telegard                      - RBBS-PC
	- TriTel                        - GAP
	- Synchronet (Use DORINFOx.DEF)   
	
   COMMUNICATIONS:
	 
	- Support for FOSSILS, internal communications to 115,200, and 
	  non-standard communication ports.  
	- Monitors carrier detect signal and returns to BBS
	- Correctly detects a keyboard timeout and returns to BBS
	- Monitors the time remaining, and returns to BBS
	- Function keys for sysops to alter user time, chat, etc...

   MULTINODE SUPPORT

	- File locking and sharing using SHARE.EXE for ALL critical files
	  including the data and log files.
	- Gives up time slices for popular multitaskers including Desqview, 
	  OS/2 and Windows
	- Individual logfiles for each node.
	
   INTER-BBS SUPPORT

	- Extremely simple for Sysops to set up, and extremely simple for 
	  the League Coodinator to maintain the league.
	- The League Coordinator handles all of the routing in the INTERBBS.CFG
	  file (see INTERBBS.DOC for info).  All other sysops simply sit back
	  and enjoy the game.
	- The league coordinator can automatically update all other systems by
	  placing the files that have changed into the OUT directory under the
	  GAC_FC directory.
	- Automatically does maintenance when the first player enters the game
	  or when the GAC_FC MAINTAIN parameter is used (only does it once/day)
	- Anyone in the league can develop a routing bulletin by using the 
	  GAC_FC ROUTE command.  This will list version numbers, route times, and
	  more about each BBS in the league.
	- All player data is shared among the BBS systems, and users may send
	  telegrams to each other from within the game using colors and a
	  ANSI editor (if they have ANSI).
	- All BBSs in the League can be forced to use the same configuration
	  parameters, thus insuring all BBSs are running identical games.
	- Checks for duplicate players, and only allows a given user name 
	  (their real name) to be used on one system at a time.
	- Will not import information from BBS not listed in the current
	  INTERBBS.CFG file.
	- The league coordinator can cause a reset of the game at any time
	  by simply using a command line switch (GAC_FC RESET)
	- Any SysOp in the League can use the SENDALL command line paramter
	  to send a personal NetMail to all of the other SysOps in a League.
	  Excellent for coordinators to keep members informed
	- A BBS can particpate in multiple leagues, as long as each league
	  has a unique three letter League ID.

   MISCELANEOUS:

	- An easy to use configuration program built in, eliminating the need
	  to edit configuration files by hand (GAC_FC CONFIG)
	- Creates bulletins showing high scores (GAC_FC BULLETINS)
	- Support for ANSI, AVATAR, ASCII and RIP (currently only uses RIP to
	  set a 23x80 screen font, thus insuring that the user does not have a
	  squashed screen effect.)
	- All artwork is now in .ART files to save disk space!
	- Written in C/C++ for the fastest, smallest code possible
	- Extensively tested both internally and through betas.
	- Reasonable prices



