³                          Installation Instructions                        ³ 
ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÙ

	NOTE: SHARE.EXE should be loaded if you want to run this program.
	
        A Windows 95/NT versions has been included in the archive.  To use
	the 32bit version unpack the WIN95NT.ZIP file and read the file 
        WIN95NT.DOC.
		
	1 - Unpack all of these files into their own directory, a good name 
		is GAC_FC.

		e.g. md c:\gac_fc
		

	2 - change to the directory where the files were placed and execute
		GAC_FC with the CONFIG option.

		e.g. GAC_FC CONFIG

	3 - Answer the questions about your system, and then exit.  Be sure
		to save the information

	4 - Setup your BBS program to run GAC_FC.BAT and pass the current node
		number to the program as the first parameter.  If needed the path 
		to your drop file should be the second parameter if you can not 
		specify it in the configuration program (e.g. each node has a 
		different path).

		e.g.  GAC_FC.BAT %#     is placed on the EXEC line in Synchronet

		NOTE: The batch file must be used so auto-updating of your GAC_FC.EXE
		file can take place during maintenance.  Please call the batch file
		anytime you access Tournament FreeCell.

		If you need batch files to run the program, pass the node number
		to the RUN.BAT file.  The RUN.BAT file should contain the 
		following lines of code.

		@Echo off
		REM RUN.BAT for GAC_FC
		REM
		REM Change to the GAC_FC directory
		c:
		cd\gac_fc
		REM Run GAC_FC passing the node number
		call gac_fc %1
		REM
		REM Change back to your bbs directory
		cd\bbs

	5 - If you want to make sure that maintenance occurs at midnight (good
		for sending long distance IBBS packets at night) then use the 
		MAINTAIN parameter.  Otherwise maintenance will take place the first
		time a user logs into the game.

		e.g.   c:
		   cd\GAC_FC
		   GAC_FC MAINTAIN
	
	6 - Test the game locally and remotely.  If you encounter a problem,
		please notify us, so we may help.

		e.g. GAC_FC 3 local     will cause local playing on node 3

	NOTE: For Inter-BBS play, see the next section

