³                              Inter-BBS Setup                              ³
ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÙ

	First thing you need to do is find a Tournament FreeCell league to
	join and apply or find some boards who want to start a new league.
	
	If you are starting a new league, then someone must be the League 
	Coordinator (BBS #1).  This person is responsible for creating the 
	INTERBBS.CFG file that you will be using, deciding which values will 
	be used for the game options, and sending the INTERBBS.CFG file to 
	all particpating systems manually the first time or by using the 
	SENDCONFIG command line parameter anytime after the first time.

	Remember, everyone participating must be running a fidonet compatible
	mailer, or find some way to pass the files to each other.

	NOTE: If you are the league coodinator, see the INTERBBS.DOC file for
	information on its format.

	Everyone in the league will have to perform the following steps.

	1 - Notify the coordinator that you want to join his/her league.

	2 - Fill in the extra Inter-BBS options in the configuration file
		using the CONFIG command line option.  This information includes  
		your league tag, netmail address, inbound file directory and
		netmail directory.

	3 - Get the INTERBBS.CFG file from your league coordinator, it will
		have to be file attached to you the first time and you will place
		it in your GAC_FC directory.  All future updates to that file will
		be handled automatically by the league coordinator.

	4 - You can have your mailer run GAC_FC INBOUND whenever 
		mail is received to immediately import the incoming Inter-BBS 
		files.  Otherwise, the inbound files will be processed during the
		automaintenance.
		
		e.g.  c:
		  cd\gac_fc
		  call gac_fc.bat INBOUND
		  call gac_fc.bat OUTBOUND

	5 - Enjoy your Inter-BBS game!



