³                          Command Line Parameters                          ³
ÀÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÙ

	This door responds to the following command line parameters:

   Parameter 1:

	[Node #]  - The current node number should be passed to the program
			when it is being run as a door or in local mode.
	
	CONFIG    - Invoke the internal configuration program for specifying
			sysop configurable options.

	MAINTAIN  - Perform the nightly maintenance.  This includes updating
			the Tournamnet day, processing inbound Inter-BBS messages,
			and creating outbound Inter-BBS messages.  This can only be
			used once per day.  No effect if automaintenance occured.

	BULLETINS - Creates ANSI and ASC score bulletins for your use

	SENDALL   - Send a NetMail message to each SysOp in the League.        

	RESET     - Used by the League Coodinator (BBS #1) to immediately
			reset all BBS's in the League.  May also be used to 
			reset a local game.
	
	INBOUND   - Process inbound Inter-BBS packages immediately

	OUTBOUND  - Send outbound Inter-BBS packages immediately

	ROUTE     - Create a report showing routing times, versions, etc...

	DELETE    - Remove a player from the database

	Parameter 2:

	LOCAL     - Forces the door to run in local mode, you will be prompted
			for the name to use in the game.

	BINKLEY   - Used to make sure Binkley Terminal sysops have the outbound
				files deleted correctly.

	[Path]    - The path to your drop file may be passed as the second 
			parameter.  This will override anything in the config
			file.




